    <body>
      <div xml:id="NA357-kiḷavi">
        <p type="edition">1. itu talaimakaṉ varaivu nīṭiyaviṭattu āṟṟuval eṉpatupaṭac colliyatu.
            2. “maṉaimaruṇṭu vēṟupāṭu āyiṉāy” eṉṟa tōḻikkut talaimakaḷ colliyatūumām.</p>
        <p type="translation" xml:lang="en">1. This is what was said in order to say “I can bear it” at the time the marriage with HIM was delayed.
            2. It is also what SHE said to the confidante who said “you have undergone changes in the confusion of the house”.</p>
        </div>
      <div xml:id="NA357">
        <lg type="edition">
<l>            niṉkuṟip pevaṉō tōḻi yeṉkuṟip</l>
<l>            peṉṉoṭu nilaiyā tāyiṉu meṉṟu</l>
<l>            neñcuvaṭup paṭuttuk keṭavaṟi yātē</l>
<l>            cēṇuṟat tōṉṟuṅ kuṉṟattuk kavāaṟ</l>
<l>            peyaluḻan tulaṟiya maṇippoṟik kuṭumip</l>
<l>            pīli maññai yāluñ cōlai</l>
<l>            yaṅka ṇaṟaiya vakalvāyp paiñcuṉai</l>
<l>            yuṇka ṇoppi ṉīla maṭaicci</l>
<l>            nīralaik kalaiiya kaṇṇic</l>
<l>            cāra ṉāṭaṉō ṭāṭiya nāḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>What [was] your intention, friend?</l>
<l rend="indent4">My intention,</l>
<l rend="indent">even if it is not permanent with me always,</l>
<l>it does not know of getting lost, so that it would reproach the heart</l>
<l>– on the day [we?] played with the man from a land of slopes,</l>
<l rend="indent3">with a chaplet disarrayed by ripples of water,</l>
<l rend="indent2">having knit together blue lotuses resembling collyrium eyes</l>
<l>from the rocky wide-mouthed fresh mountain spring, a pretty place</l>
<l rend="indent">in a grove where the fanned(?) peacocks dance,</l>
<l>with sapphire-spotted crests that dried after having borne the rain</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the slope of the hill that appears in the distance<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="foot">cēṇ uṟa tōṉṟum</term>: what can be the significance of <term xml:lang="foot">uṟa</term> here?</note>.</l>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
